We have a cEDH guy showing up the last couple of weeks, and he's the cliched cEDH guy too, talks shit about everyone's deck, is way too loud and obnoxius about flashing Hulk, etc. He tried to get into pods all night and got shut down and spent like two hours sitting by himself fucking around on his phone. One guy flat out said "No, we're full, but if I'm being honest I'd rather go home than play with you."
So that problem seems to have solved itself
Classic.
it turns out, being a dick makes people not like you
unless you're <@U32LRG9NU>

Oh wow.
I remember looking it up because it feels the cEDH is pretty insular with LabManiacs and a few other prominent members.
I think it was something like... 6 members were responsible for 14/20 of the tier cEDH decks on the list I looked at

I super don’t mind cEDH folks, I just do want them to know the time and place for it. I’ve built decks that are accidentally too good and when I do, I scale that shit back; a lot of my group has only been playing for like a year or two. It’s just a matter of tact
There’s always been a natural arms race in my playgroups and we always seem to get there, but we inevitably scrap the decks once they hit a certain point and start over.
I just have no desire to play out the same combo every game
the best part about my play group before they moved was that there was a couple who hated each other's decks out no matter the deck, mostly because they played against each other all the time
Our league title champion's deck is Teferi Chain Veil, and his reasoning is that he gets targeted first so he might as well play combo.
Self fulfilling prophecy
I know. It doesn't help that trying to hate that deck out feeds into his ego. Need to find a way to passively deal with a tier 1 cEDH deck. Ugh.
